              "type": "uniqueValue",
              "valueExpression": "var lessthan25 = $feature.Estimate_Total_Lessthan10000+$feature.Estimate_Total_10000to14999+$feature.Estimate_Total_15000to19999+$feature.Estimate_Total_20000to24999;\r\nvar range25to50 = $feature.Estimate_Total_25000to29999+$feature.Estimate_Total_30000to34999+$feature.Estimate_Total_35000to39999+$feature.Estimate_Total_40000to44999+$feature.Estimate_Total_45000to49999;\r\nvar range50to100 = $feature.Estimate_Total_50000to59999+$feature.Estimate_Total_60000to74999+$feature.Estimate_Total_75000to99999\r\nvar range100plus = $feature.Estimate_Total_100000to124999+$feature.Estimate_Total_125000to149999+$feature.Estimate_Total_150000to199999+$feature.Estimate_Total_200000ormore ;\r\n\r\n\r\n// The fields from which to calculate predominance\r\n// The expression will return the alias of the predominant field\r\n\r\nvar fields = [\r\n  { value: lessthan25, alias: \"Households making less than $25,000\" },\r\n  { value: range25to50, alias: \"Households making $25,000 to $50,000\" },\r\n  { value: range50to100, alias: \"Households making $50,000 to $100,000\" },\r\n  { value: range100plus, alias: \"Households making $100,000 or more\" }\r\n];\r\n\r\n// Returns the predominant category as the alias\r\n// defined in the fields array. If there is a tie,\r\n// then both names are concatenated and used to\r\n// indicate the tie\r\n\r\nfunction getPredominantCategory(fieldsArray){\r\n  var maxValue = -Infinity;\r\n  var maxCategory = \"\";\r\n  for(var k in fieldsArray){\r\n    if(fieldsArray[k].value > maxValue){\r\n      maxValue = fieldsArray[k].value;\r\n      maxCategory = fieldsArray[k].alias;\r\n    } else if (fieldsArray[k].value == maxValue){\r\n      maxCategory = maxCategory + \"/\" + fieldsArray[k].alias;\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n  return IIF(maxValue <= 0, null, maxCategory);\r\n}\r\n\r\ngetPredominantCategory(fields);",
